  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legislative Frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture mechanisms\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory oversight\n- Criminal prosecution\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions' due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Internal control systems\n\n6. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have unique legal approaches\n- Varying definitions and thresholds\n- Specific regulatory requirements\n\n7. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Cross-border financial tracking\n\nThese elements collectively form a comprehensive legal framework addressing money laundering prevention and prosecution.",
